    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="859"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d859">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.48 Earthquake of 1931/95: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName> [<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-07">undated</date>].<lb/>[Received
                        April 7, 1931—11:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Relief measures continue satisfactorily. Other Central American countries doing
                    valuable work. Health conditions are good. Four <pb facs="0917" n="797"
                        xml:id="pg_797"/> thousand persons inoculated against typhoid today and a
                    like number will be inoculated tomorrow.</p>
                <p>Through rail communication to Corinto will probably be reestablished Thursday.
                    Families are slowly returning to their homes and are repairing them. The efforts
                    of the Central Relief Committee are being concentrated on the problems of
                    shelter and of restoring normal living and commercial conditions in the
                    community.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
